21.21	Copa_Am%C3%A9rica_2007	2007 Copa América	The 2007 Campeonato Sudamericano Copa América, known simply as the 2007 Copa América or 2007 Copa América Venezuela, was the 42nd edition of the Copa América, the South-American championship for international association football teams. The competition was organized by CONMEBOL, South America's football governing body, and was held in Venezuela, who hosted the tournament for the first time, between June 26 and July 15, 2007. The defending champion was Brazil.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/36/2007_Copa_Am%C3%A9rica_logo.svg/200px-2007_Copa_Am%C3%A9rica_logo.svg.png
